Guangxi college students can take a break from school to start a business for up to 5 years - Xinhua Xinhua News Agency, Nanning, May 19 (Reporter Zhang Ying) reporter recently learned from the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region Department of Education, Guangxi colleges and universities will implement a flexible school system in the future, relax the number of years students take a break from school, students can take a break from school to start a business for 2 to 5 years on the basis of the original school system, the time off from school to start a business can be considered as practical education time. In order to promote the entrepreneurial and innovative ability of college students, Guangxi education, human resources and other departments work together to build a platform for entrepreneurship, and build more off-campus practice teaching bases for college students, university science and technology parks, college student business parks, business incubation bases, etc., to provide external protection for college students' entrepreneurship. According to the requirements, by 2020, the area of innovation and entrepreneurship practice bases in each university should reach more than 3,000 square meters for undergraduate schools and more than 2,000 square meters for higher vocational schools. The government encourages universities to set up innovation and entrepreneurship credits and give priority to support students who excel in innovation and entrepreneurship practice to change their majors. Teachers in colleges and universities should have at least two months of attachment to industry enterprises every two years, so as to improve the awareness and ability of teachers in innovation and entrepreneurship education. The Department of Education of the autonomous region requires all colleges and universities in Guangxi to deeply implement the innovation and entrepreneurship training program for college students, and strive to make every college student participate in an innovation and entrepreneurship training program during school. Colleges and universities should actively organize students to participate in various innovation and entrepreneurship competitions at all levels, and give financial support.
